tweet: WV doesn’t have a centralized criminal prosecutorial system unlike most states. When allegations of sexual abuse arise across WV, there is no organized mechanism for prosecuting these crimes. Sadly, local prosecutors — under huge pressure locally— don’t always bring charges.
